  intuition: String.raw`<p>The concrete problem is that the unconstrained best point may be illegal. If a constraint blocks the downhill direction, the optimum can live on a boundary with nonzero objective gradient.</p><p>The mental model is force balance. The objective pulls downhill; active constraints push back along their normals. At optimum, no feasible movement improves the objective.</p><p>The design decision is to attach a multiplier to each constraint. A multiplier is the price of tightening that constraint, and complementarity says only active walls can charge a price.</p>`,
